= toys-c
Al Idian <al.idian@acm.org>
:description: A collection of (very) small programs in c

`toys` is a collection of (very) small programs, each meant to show just one or two competencies.

Setup:

[source,bash]
----
# Start a toolbox container
docker run --name toys-c -it -v "$(pwd)":/home/idianal/toys-c idianal/toolbox

# Inside the container, install required packages
apt update
apt install -y build-essential

# Test the environment
cd toys-c/foo-bar
git clone https://github.com/ThrowTheSwitch/Unity.git unity
make -s test
----
